  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "offer_browser_tts": "false",
    "panels": [
      {
        "text": "### Effects\n\n**Effects** are a way for record producers to change how a track sounds",
        "imageUrl": "https://images.code.org/e86c2910cd1d5b6a08d1b8837fb0685a-Slide15.PNG",
        "key": "test-music-lab-sequences-synthesize-effects-panel-7e5c491e-8f2d-458f-bd0d-931757763830",
        "fadeInOverPrevious": true
      },
      {
        "text": "### Effects\n\nYou can use them with different tracks to change how a song sounds or feels.\n\nIn this example, the backing tracks will be at a lower volume than the main chorus",
        "imageUrl": "https://images.code.org/fd999fa77181492711f25bfa9c2aa3fc-Slide16.PNG",
        "key": "test-music-lab-sequences-synthesize-effects-panel-dd8d2de9-1cb7-4261-9f69-12853bc8e8a3",
        "fadeInOverPrevious": true
      },
      {
        "text": "### Effects\n\n**Sequencing is important with effects!** \n\nOnce you set an effect, it applies to every block that comes after it unless you change it",
        "imageUrl": "https://images.code.org/1f4f0e954d2111144407297e412834a3-Slide18.PNG",
        "key": "test-music-lab-sequences-synthesize-effects-panel-45513791-722a-4ac8-a8c3-d313b8f2ece6",
        "fadeInOverPrevious": true
      },
      {
        "text": "### Effects\n\nYou can also set multiple effects and they will all apply together",
        "imageUrl": "https://images.code.org/2af203c568e7aed8fc39baaa7e3dbfe4-Slide20.PNG",
        "key": "test-music-lab-sequences-synthesize-effects-panel-acacf059-9690-455c-b595-62395ff70216",
        "fadeInOverPrevious": true
      },
      {
        "text": "### Effects\n\nThere are three types of effects available in Music Lab: volume, filter, and delay.\n\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-pencil\"></i> **Volume**: Changes the loudness of the function\n\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-pencil\"></i> **Filter**: Changes the tone of the function, making the sounds muted or muffled\n\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-pencil\"></i> **Delay**: Adds an echo to the sounds",
        "imageUrl": "https://images.code.org/98982b27525bcfa8b6a42d01ba55242a-Slide21.PNG",
        "key": "test-music-lab-sequences-synthesize-effects-panel-8a25ec76-0628-4559-969a-75bb36410c9c",
        "fadeInOverPrevious": true,
        "layout": "text-bottom-center"
      },
      {
        "text": "Key Takeaway: Effect blocks change how a song sounds and feels. They affect all of the blocks that come after them. ",
        "imageUrl": "https://images.code.org/853122ec8b06b4cb461810f1d798fd9a-Slide22.PNG",
        "key": "test-music-lab-sequences-synthesize-effects-panel-ea91d99a-914c-4c48-8336-818e8e7feba8",
        "fadeInOverPrevious": true,
        "typing": true
      }
    ],
    "name_suffix": "_v2"
  },
